org.bukkit.event

注釈型 EventHandler


  • @Target(value=METHOD)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface EventHandler
    An annotation to mark methods as being event handler methods

    • 任意要素のサマリー

      任意要素 
      修飾子とタイプ 任意要素と説明
      boolean ignoreCancelled
      Define if the handler ignores a cancelled event.
      EventPriority priority
      Define the priority of the event.

    • 要素の詳細

      • priority

        public abstract EventPriority priority
        Define the priority of the event.

        First priority to the last priority executed:

        1. LOWEST
        2. LOW
        3. NORMAL
        4. HIGH
        5. HIGHEST
        6. MONITOR
        戻り値:
        the priority
        デフォルト:
        org.bukkit.event.EventPriority.NORMAL

      • ignoreCancelled

        public abstract boolean ignoreCancelled
        Define if the handler ignores a cancelled event.

        If ignoreCancelled is true and the event is cancelled, the method is not called. Otherwise, the method is always called.

        戻り値:
        whether cancelled events should be ignored
        デフォルト:
        false
